
<div class="container">

  <section>
    <h2>What is a 1D Cellular Automaton?</h2>
    <div>
    A model in which a sequence of characters change over time based on a collection of simple rules.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>

    <h2>How it Works:</h2>
    <div>
    Create a sequence of 0's and 1's, such as:
      <p>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
    Define some rules for triplets of 0's and 1's, such as:
      <p>
        <div class="row triplet_rules">
          <div class="col-md-3 col-md-offset-1">
            <ul>
              <li>100 becomes 1</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-3">
            <ul>
              <li>001 becomes 1</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-5">
            <ul>
              <li>Other triplets become 0</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
    Apply the rules to each successive triplet in the first sequence to get a new sequence.
    Below, only the triplet 001 leads to a 1, and ends of the new sequence are assigned 0.
      <p>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
    Repeat. Applying the rules again gives:
      <p>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-md-4 col-md-offset-4">
            <div class="col-md-3"></div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 1 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
            <div class="col-md-1"> 0 </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>

  <div class="center_button">
    <%= link_to "Create a Model", one_dim_rules_path, class: "btn btn-primary btn-lg" %>
  </div>

</div>
